1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:08,000
Good ideas arrive while you're moving, then disappear inside a long voice note.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:16,000
Nugget starts with one tap: capture first, organize later.

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:29,000
The voice-first screen stays deliberately simple. I can speak naturally, watch the live waveform, and stop when the thought is out of my head.

4
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:49,000
The recording is saved in this browser before cloud processing begins. Nugget can transcribe the audio, organize the transcript, and return a reviewable result without losing the source.

5
00:00:49,000 --> 00:01:02,000
For this interface walkthrough, I'm switching to a clearly disclosed, preprocessed safe capture. One ramble has become three separate idea drafts.

6
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:18,000
Each draft is editable before I trust it: title, summary, category, tags, goals, blockers, research needs, and next actions. Grounding labels show how every field relates to the source.

7
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Confirmed ideas become a searchable local library. This view uses Nugget's labeled sample data, so it does not make a new GPT call.

8
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:47,000
Opening an idea keeps its summary, category, tags, goals, blockers, research, and next actions together instead of burying the useful parts back inside a transcript.

9
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:55,000
I captured this feature idea in Nugget itself. That saved thought became what you're seeing now.

10
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:09,000
Work with this idea can explore a thought, create a plan, or prepare a grounded brief for another AI. The source transcript stays off unless I explicitly include it.

11
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:13,000
I confirm exactly what is sent, then GPT-5.6 gets to work.

12
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:37,000
The result is a structured, editable brief with an objective, context, assumptions, constraints, deliverables, and success criteria. It stays grounded in the organized idea, labels missing context instead of inventing it, and produces a prompt I can copy or download.

13
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:46,000
Settings keeps the privacy boundary visible and reports live Whisper and GPT-5.6 Terra health.

14
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:51,200
Nugget captures ideas and helps bring them into the real world.
